					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The record belongs to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Akālavarsha.</hi> The beginning of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of Kuppeyarasa of the Yādava family who was a subordinate of Amōghavarsha I (above No. 12) is preserved. It is probable, therefore, that he might have been mentioned here. If so, the record will have to be assigned to Kṛishṇa II. Aṇṇigeṟe is mentioned. Reference to Kannara is noteworthy.</p>						

						</summary>
